The paper discusses the impact of the Digital Transformation on society, which involves a wide range of topics related to computer science. The most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which specifically deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. The paper also covers issues related to information technology (cs.IT), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and social networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the study methodology involves an online real-time Delphi study, which could fall under the category of social informatics (cs.SI).
